  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Rib fractures are the most frequent injury after blunt thoracic trauma. It is very important&#xD;
      to choose the most appropriate interventions to prevent complications. But who will benefit&#xD;
      most of those interventions remains a challenge.&#xD;
&#xD;
      This study analyses the correlation between chest X-Ray and CT scan. We also analyse&#xD;
      different scores to predict respiratory failure.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
